---
title: Double Indian Beef Biryani & DIY Onion Bhajis Take your cooking skills to the next level!
description: Time to unleash your inner chef! We’re looking for a new challenge, and we think it’s the perfect time to try recreating a couple of Indian classics - biryani and onion bhajis. The biryani is deeply flavourful, with Bengal curry paste and punchy ginger paste cooked right into the rice, and beef mince and roast veggies tossed through. Then there’s the onion bhajis - these funky-shaped, crispy golden bites are a true joy to eat, and are just as fun to make. Let’s get started!

*This recipe is under 650kcal per serving.*
